{
  "text": "However, recent studies have concluded that less invasive methods, such as percutaneous transcatheter embolization, are preferable [CITATION_1] . To occlude the ITA side branch safely and effectively, some principles are recommended. First, the possibility of damaging the ITA should be minimized by using a small-diameter delivery system with a smooth distal section.",
  "citation_candidates": [
